replies.bodyText:
This is the intended logic flow:

The user specifies options, cruise.control.metrics.topic.num.partitions and/or cruise.control.metrics.topic.replication.factor in the Kafka.spec.kafka.config
These options are read
The if-statements highlighted above will not execute since they are found in the map with getConfigOption(), so the fields ccNumPartitions and ccReplicationFactor will remain null
The ccNumPartitions and ccReplicationFactor fields are passed to  KafkaBrokerConfigurationBuilder, but will not be added to the broker configuration since they are null. This way these options are only added once to the broker configuration.



